UID:ae7b301567175bbc3e7d934fa0eb2c8d@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Join a park naturalist for a guided hike of Trail 2. This trai
 l features several unique structures built by the Civilian Conservation Co
 rps\, or CCC. Learn about the origin and purpose of the CCC\, and how they
  helped build the Indiana State Parks we all enjoy even today! Trail 2 is 
 two miles long and considered moderate. It has uneven surfaces\, staircase
 s\, slopes\, and possible muddy spots. It will take us about an hour and a
  half to complete.
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Abe Martin Lodge (lobby)\, 1405 S.R. 46
  W\, Nashville\, IN 
